parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Auxiliary Selector Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank auxiliary selector valve can cause fuel to overflow from the filler cap, leading to a fire hazard, decreased fuel mileage, and potential health risks from fuel fumes.
symptoms: Fuel gushes out when opening the gas cap
fuel spills onto the ground while filling up
unused fuel returns to the front tank when it's full
fuel leakage from the auxiliary tank
fuel fumes emitted from the tank

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the engine to stall or overheat, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially resulting in accidents or engine fires.
symptoms: the catalytic converter becomes plugged without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling issue can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds in hot weather.
symptoms: the vehicle stalls suddenly and unexpectedly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The driveability problems can cause a loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds in hot weather.
symptoms: the vehicle has a serious driveability problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially if it occurs at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
